Linus and Luke debate the idea of banning ransomware payments after an Economist article suggests it could curb cybercrime. They argue it’s an appealing idea in theory but unrealistic in practice. Criminals will adapt, companies will still pay secretly, and there’s never a true silver bullet solution.
